The White House Office of the Press Secretary has released a message to the Senate regarding a treaty between the United States and the Republic of Kazakhstan on Mutual Legal Assistance in Criminal Matters. The treaty, signed on February 20, 2015, is part of a series of agreements aimed at improving international cooperation in combating criminal activities. It covers a wide range of areas, including the production of evidence, arranging for witnesses to travel to another country, serving documents, executing searches and seizures, locating individuals or items, and freezing and forfeiting assets related to criminal activity. The President recommends that the Senate consider and ratify the treaty.